# Accessibility Standards

Accessibility is mandatory — not a polish pass.

## Must support

- Full keyboard navigation
- Visible focus states
- Screen readers (semantic HTML + ARIA only when needed)
- Adequate color contrast
- `prefers-reduced-motion` respected
- Usable without a mouse

## Forms

- Every input has a visible `<label>`
- Errors are associated with fields
- Required fields indicated
- Do not rely on color alone for meaning

## Interactive targets

Touch-friendly hit areas on mobile. Icon-only buttons need accessible names.

## Modals / dialogs

Focus trap, Escape to close, restore focus on dismiss, announce title.
